						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone lying near the temple of Īśvara.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription states that <hi rend="bold">Male-Nāyaka,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Maṅge-Nāyaka,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">mādāra</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Maṇṭagaṇī</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Male-Nāyaka,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Maḷe Nāyaka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Yettinahaḷḷi,</hi> together gave half of the <hi rend="italic">mādārike</hi> of Maṇṭagaṇi to <hi rend="bold">Girige-Nāyaka</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Gaṅga</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Malla,</hi> the sons of <hi rend="bold">Chandeya-Nāyaka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kaḷasūr.</hi></p>						

						<p>The date of this record is lost. It is written in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">17th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
